{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ulsch_scheduler_pre_processor function behavior\n\n### Summary\nThe `ulsch_scheduler_pre_processor` function in the eNB scheduler was not behaving as expected due to several issues in the UL scheduling algorithm implementation. These issues caused incorrect RB allocation and scheduling decisions for UEs.\n\nThe root cause was:\n1. Incorrect initialization of the `start_ue` value in the setup function\n2. Not handling the return value of the UL scheduling algorithm run function\n3. Commented out lines that set the `pre_allocated_nb_rb_ul` field\n4. Incorrect order of assignment and logging in the retransmission case\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/pre_processor.c`: \n  - Fixed initialization of `start_ue` value in `rr_ul_setup` function from 0 to -1\n  - Fixed order of assignment and logging in retransmission case\n  - Uncommented lines that set the `pre_allocated_nb_rb_ul` field for both pending scheduling requests and normal allocations\n  - Handled return value of UL scheduling algorithm run function in `ulsch_scheduler_pre_processor`\n\n"
}